<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851.248/185: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-26T17:00:00-05:00">April 26, 1939—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>313. Your No. 817, April 25, 9 a.m. I assume that the Minister for
                                Air, in connection with his plans for the purchase of Allison
                                engines, is bearing in mind the provisions of Section 1 (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) and Section 5 (<hi rend="italic">g</hi>)
                                of the Neutrality Act.<note n="51" xml:id="d461fn51">50 Stat.
                                    121.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>